51
00:03:31.750 --> 00:03:36.070
First, hydraulic sensors, or hydraulic actuators I should say,

52
00:03:36.070 --> 00:03:40.300
use pressure from highly compressed oil to push large cylinders

53
00:03:40.300 --> 00:03:45.670
inside construction equipment such as lifts, cranes, and excavators.

54
00:03:45.670 --> 00:03:50.260
They're characterized by slow speed of response due to the long time it

55
00:03:50.260 --> 00:03:55.945
takes to compressed oil and the high gear ratios in the mechanisms that deploy them.

56
00:03:55.945 --> 00:03:59.645
Pneumatic actuators give a faster speed of

57
00:03:59.645 --> 00:04:04.385
response due to a faster compression of air versus oil.

58
00:04:04.385 --> 00:04:08.045
They're most commonly found in production assembly equipment.

59
00:04:08.045 --> 00:04:09.730
The downside is they're

60
00:04:09.730 --> 00:04:16.341
really noisy and small leaks in these seals lead to large losses in compression.

