00:04:16.341 --> 00:04:21.790
Electrical motors convert electrical energy to rotary motion.

62
00:04:21.790 --> 00:04:24.730
They are directly interfaced with sensors within

63
00:04:24.730 --> 00:04:29.380
hardware and will be used extensively in our course.

64
00:04:29.380 --> 00:04:32.200
Mechanical actuators such as gears,

65
00:04:32.200 --> 00:04:33.988
and belts, and lead screws,

66
00:04:33.988 --> 00:04:38.980
either they boost up the torque or they convert the rotary motion to linear motion.

67
00:04:38.980 --> 00:04:43.295
Electrical actuators come in three flavors.

68
00:04:43.295 --> 00:04:48.715
A stepper motor has multiple coils organized in phases.

69
00:04:48.715 --> 00:04:52.120
Energizing the coils sequentially allows

70
00:04:52.120 --> 00:04:56.355
the stepper motor to rotate in very precise steps.

71
00:04:56.355 --> 00:05:03.980
A brushed DC motor has a coil that generates a magnetic field around that armature.

72
00:05:03.980 --> 00:05:09.220
One side of that armature is repelled by the north pole of a magnet located

73
00:05:09.220 --> 00:05:14.950
in the motor casing while the other side is attracted to the south pole of that magnet.

74
00:05:14.950 --> 00:05:20.620
The opposing forces cause the armature to rotate in one direction.

75
00:05:20.620 --> 00:05:23.305
As the armature rotates in that direction,

76
00:05:23.305 --> 00:05:26.170
the torque eventually goes to zero and

77
00:05:26.170 --> 00:05:30.610
the magnetic field of the armature attracts to the north and south poles.

78
00:05:30.610 --> 00:05:36.486
Reversing current to the armature causes that side to be repelled by the south pole,

79
00:05:36.486 --> 00:05:40.690
but attracted to the north pole and reversing

80
00:05:40.690 --> 00:05:46.080
current exactly on that half cycle creates your continuous rotation.

81
00:05:46.080 --> 00:05:49.800
The brushes in the brushed DC motors

82
00:05:49.800 --> 00:05:54.442
wear rapidly and must be replaced at frequent intervals.

83
00:05:54.442 --> 00:05:58.420
Brushless DC motors resolved this issue by

84
00:05:58.420 --> 00:06:03.430
using permanent magnets rotating around a fixed armature.

85
00:06:03.430 --> 00:06:06.850
An electronic controller switches the phase to

86
00:06:06.850 --> 00:06:10.720
the windings allowing rotation within the motor.

